<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Inline Assessment MathML 1.4//EN" "http://oli.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_inline_assessment_mathml_1_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="newe0716f25fc5745349105335f247c8684"><title>Functional and N-F Requirements</title><page id="a367d395e7fd4016abb5cd3a1e172f5d"><title>Page 1</title><question id="newe0716f25fc5745349105335f247c8684_1a"><body><p id="eea60cc25e6c4b3c84b7cd489bd59c94">A description of a task that a system will perform under specific conditions is called:</p></body><multiple_choice shuffle="false" select="single" id="ans" labels="false"><choice value="yes">Non-Functional Requirements.</choice><choice value="no">Functional Requirements.</choice><choice value="cfdf72f837074bd1a3c62d823d126e3d">Quality attributes.</choice></multiple_choice><part id="addd235fe8914cf28a2a40146bc98b4c"><skillref idref="a8280995691d4e7f80f2fa50cfd7557b" /><response match="yes" score="0"><feedback><p id="ebb6b11ee6134684820871728550179e">Incorrect:  Non-functional requirements are characteristics of a system.</p></feedback></response><response match="no" score="1"><feedback><p id="d0ae390c8ede4d5b8991f0aab87e3f8d">Correct: In addition this &quot;behavior&quot; will enable users to accomplish their interact with the system.</p></feedback></response><response match="cfdf72f837074bd1a3c62d823d126e3d" score="0"><feedback><p id="ed2ba92079fb488ab6eb2fed216f2b8c">Incorrect: This is a non-functional requirement that defines the performance of a system. </p></feedback></response></part></question><question id="a3aa59bbf9bf42aea1d70d26b6f45800"><body><p id="a0142ffcc95d442c8a9a0eb8e4184fba">A functional requirement can be decomposed from a user requirement and:</p></body><multiple_choice shuffle="true" select="single" id="e59b3bda11e04cedb7cbb1f3d7b2f2a4" labels="false"><choice value="e20dfd5cda1c415581af629b1c18bbb9">Business Rules.</choice><choice value="d65f4549f7744755b03f00908571b795">Execution Qualities.</choice><choice value="d3f2f718d98041338e5607a0f74f829c">Standard System Attributes.</choice></multiple_choice><part id="efcf2175649849ada14760392b64a09b"><skillref idref="a8280995691d4e7f80f2fa50cfd7557b" /><response match="e20dfd5cda1c415581af629b1c18bbb9" score="1"><feedback><p id="dc1710d6ebff45139936d1b8969f194f">Correct: Business rules are guidelines that define parts of a business. Business rules influence business, user and  therefore, functional requirements. </p></feedback></response><response match="d65f4549f7744755b03f00908571b795" score="0"><feedback><p id="c97a904af4244a24b481de6f3462e86c">Incorrect: In software engineering, execution qualities such as safety, usability and security are non functional requirements</p></feedback></response><response match="d3f2f718d98041338e5607a0f74f829c" score="0"><feedback><p id="f1f22d3cfa8d4a3fb802bc368ac0c962">Incorrect: System attributes are simply characteristics of the system which are also non-functional in nature.</p></feedback></response></part></question><question id="df078e6674254388ba7250c860578c20"><body><p id="e7fd92e7b56f4760b1f203f4e06c13e6">A business analyst is defining the requirements for the development of a learning management system for an institution. Each time a user is unsuccessful in their attempt to access the LMS, &quot;those attempts are recorded on an audit trail&quot;. This requirement would be considered a(n):</p></body><multiple_choice shuffle="true" select="single" id="dbee5a58d5414dc39c18c984f1a6bd56" labels="false"><choice value="b1b41ef0ffef42cba083a8c7f3f35ae8">Complete functional requirement.</choice><choice value="d5c7e0b0ae52443abcec65ff3058d72a">Business requirement.</choice><choice value="a215ac48e9494e4db7ddbe136db5d70a">Non-functional requirement.</choice></multiple_choice><part id="a6cffd1805f842a88185c4efe39d17d6"><skillref idref="a83a3d76c7ca4b11b14be98ba673dcfe" /><response match="b1b41ef0ffef42cba083a8c7f3f35ae8" score="0"><feedback><p id="d5506ba4fedd41529827890ab6dc1556">Incorrect: This is a non-functional requirement. A functional requirement is this scenario would refer to what a user can do with the system. This scenario highlights what auditability which is a security or operational requirement.</p></feedback></response><response match="d5c7e0b0ae52443abcec65ff3058d72a" score="0"><feedback><p id="bf989d4e9cc14a85b837749253d94eb5">Incorrect: Business requirements describe why the business needs a system or solution. This is a feature within the solution.</p></feedback></response><response match="a215ac48e9494e4db7ddbe136db5d70a" score="1"><feedback><p id="ac3f5d1ff6f34b81b5db578510cddf75">Correct: This is an operational requirement that considers the security of the system.</p></feedback></response></part></question></page></assessment>
